Say it Together! Basic Japanese Words in Japanese Alphabetical Order
Today's Word is "SU" SUMO　#nihongo　#sumo

Is there any sumo wrestlers from your country?

body.text: Since it's a cultural exchange i would like to ask what the japanese language partners would like to know about the asean member countries cultures, too. Are these partners coming to help to spread japanese culture and language throughout the world ? Is that the aim of the project ?? Or will the partners be also traveling for tourism ?? Would by any chance, Brazil be among those mentioned asean countries ?? If yes, i would like to volunteer as a consultant to help those partners on techniques about how to teach japanese language to brazilians as well as for tips and warnings while they're here.

message.text:
KANJI Quiz!
Do you know the meaning of the Kanji "夢中"？ Choose the answer!
1. in a trance 2. obstacle 3. together

Do you have anything/anyone you are into right now? 
In Japan, it has been a perfect weather for going outside and find something interesting!   
http://www.anime-manga.jp/KanjiGame/Love/　　
「夢中」の意味はどれ？天気も気持ちいいし、夢中になれるものを探しに行こう！
